select concat(first_name, " ",last_name) as full_name
from patients;

select first_name, last_name, max(height)
from patients;

select * from patients
where patient_id in (1,45,534,879,1000);

select count(*) as total_admission
from admissions;

select * from admissions
where admission_date = discharge_date;

select distinct city from patients
where province_id = "NS";

select first_name, last_name, birth_date
from patients
where height > 160
and weight > 70;

select patients.patient_id, first_name, last_name
from patients
join admissions ad On ad.patient_id = patients.patient_id
where ad.diagnosis = "Dementia";

select first_name from patients
order by len(first_name), first_name;

select 
count(case when gender = "M" then 1 end) as Numer_of_Men, 
count(case when gender = "F" then 1 end) as Number_of_women
from patients;

select first_name, last_name, allergies
from patients
where allergies IN ("Penicillin", "Morphine")
order by 3, 1,2;

select patients.patient_id, ad.diagnosis
from patients
join admissions ad on ad.patient_id = patients.patient_id
group by patients.patient_id, ad.diagnosis
having count(*) >1;

select city, count(*) as city_pop
from patients
group by city
order by city_pop desc, city;

select distinct year(birth_date) as birth_year
from patients
order by birth_year;

select city, count(*) as city_pop
from patients
group by city
order by city_pop desc, city;


select first_name, last_name, "Patient" as role
from patients
union
select first_name, last_name, "Doctor" as role
from doctors;

select first_name, last_name, birth_date
from patients
where year(birth_date) between 1970 and 1979
order by birth_date;

select province_id, sum(height) as total_height
from patients
group by province_id
having total_height >= 7000;

select day(admission_date) as days, count(*) as freg
from admissions
group by days
order by  freg desc;

select * from admissions
where patient_id = 542
order by admission_date desc
limit 1;

select first_name, last_name, count(*) nos_admission
from doctors
join admissions on admissions.attending_doctor_id = doctors.doctor_id
group by doctor_id;

select doctor_id, concat(first_name," ", last_name) as full_name, 
		min(a.admission_date) as first_attendance,
        max(a.admission_date) as last_attended
from doctors d
join admissions a on a.attending_doctor_id = d.doctor_id
group by doctor_id;

select doctor_id, concat(first_name," ", last_name) as full_name, 
		min(a.admission_date) as first_attendance,
        max(a.admission_date) as last_attended
from doctors d
join admissions a on a.attending_doctor_id = d.doctor_id
group by doctor_id;

select first_name
from patients
group by first_name
having count(*) = 1;

select allergies, count(*) as popularity 
from patients
where allergies is not null
group by allergies
order by popularity desc;

select concat(p.first_name, " ",p.last_name) as patient_name,
		ad.diagnosis, concat(d.first_name, " ", d.last_name) as Doctor_name
from admissions ad
join patients p on p.patient_id = ad.patient_id
join doctors d on d.doctor_id = ad.attending_doctor_id;

select first_name, last_name, count(*) as duplicate
from patients
group by first_name, last_name
having duplicate > 1;

select concat(first_name, " ", last_name) as full_name,
		round((height / 30.48), 1) as height_In_feet,
        round((weight *2.205), 0) as weight_in_pounds,
        birth_date,
       case 
       when gender = "M" then "Male"
       when gender = "F" then "Female" end as gender
from patients;

select floor((weight /10) *10) as weight_group, count(*) as patients_in_group
from patients
group by weight_group
order by weight_group desc;

from patients p
join admissions ad on ad.patient_id = p.patient_id
where ad.patient_id = p.patient_id;

select 
	case when patient_id % 2 = 0 then "Yes"
    else "No" end as has_insurance,
    sum(case when patient_id % 2 = 0 then 10
       	 else 50 end) as cost_of_admission
from admissions
group by has_insurance;

SELECT * FROM patients

select floor((weight /10) *10) as weight_group, count(*) as patients_in_group
from patients
group by weight_group
order by weight_group desc;


select patient_id, weight, height,
	case 
		 when (weight/power(height/100, 2)) >= 30 then 1
         else 0 end as isObese
from patients;


select p.patient_id, p.first_name, p.last_name, d.specialty
from patients p
join admissions ad on ad.patient_id = p.patient_id
join doctors d on  d.doctor_id = ad.attending_doctor_id
where ad.diagnosis = "Epilepsy" and d.first_name = "Lisa";


select distinct p.patient_id, 
	   concat(p.patient_id, len(p.last_name), year(birth_date)) as temp_password
from patients p
join admissions ad on ad.patient_id = p.patient_id
where ad.patient_id = p.patient_id;

select 
	case when patient_id % 2 = 0 then "Yes"
    else "No" end as has_insurance,
    sum(case when patient_id % 2 = 0 then 10
       	 else 50 end) as cost_of_admission
from admissions
group by has_insurance;


SELECT pr.province_name
FROM patients AS pa
JOIN province_names AS pr ON pa.province_id = pr.province_id
GROUP BY pr.province_name
HAVING
COUNT( CASE WHEN gender = 'M' THEN 1 END) > COUNT( CASE WHEN gender = 'F' THEN 1 END);
